headline: Microsoft Stock Rises After Company Shoots Down Xbox Exit Rumors
summary: Microsoft (MSFT, Financials) shares ticked higher Monday after the company stepped in to squash growing rumors that it was done making Xbox consoles.  Speculation had been swirling online that the Xbox Series X and S would be the last of their kind, with Microsoft supposedly shifting to a cloud-only future centered on Xbox Game Pass.  In a statement to Windows Central, Microsoft said, We are actively investing in our future first-party consoles and devices designed, engineered and built by Xbox.
